\\n\\nI need to focus on the active class in the initialization. It sounds like I should test the text/plain behavior and write one file for that. I wonder if the ActivationDataFlavor truly ignores parameters—maybe I can assert that. My tests should cover various aspects like exposing plain string transfer flavor, reading from the data source with UTF-8, and ensuring it defaults to ASCII when the charset is absent. I hope that's sufficient, but maybe I still need to compile without running the tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4WlLLPghCo3MMiqV4PAwCv43|fc_049833e0b00739d70169f51378d5fc81a3babbd897bfb6e130", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javax.mail/mail/1.4/src/test/java/javax_mail/mail/TextPlainTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javax_mail.mail;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\nimport com.sun.mail.handlers.text_plain;\nimport java.awt.datatransfer.DataFlavor;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport javax.activation.DataSource;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class TextPlainTest {\n    private static final String MIME_TYPE = \"text/plain\";\n    private static final String PLAIN_TEXT = \"Mail handler plain text \\u2603\";\n\n    @Test\n    void exposesPlainStringTransferFlavor() {\n        text_plain handler = new text_plain();\n\n        DataFlavor[] flavors = handler.getTransferDataFlavors();\n\n        assertPlainStringFlavor(flavors);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsPlainTextContentFromDataSource() throws IOException {\n        text_plain handler = new text_plain();\n        DataFlavor flavor = handler.getTransferDataFlavors()[0];\n        DataSource dataSource = new PlainTextDataSource(PLAIN_TEXT, MIME_TYPE + \"; charset=UTF-8\");\n\n        Object transferData = handler.getTransferData(flavor, dataSource);\n\n        assertThat(transferData).isEqualTo(PLAIN_TEXT);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void returnsNullForUnsupportedTransferFlavor() throws IOException {\n        text_plain handler = new text_plain();\n        DataFlavor unsupportedFlavor = new DataFlavor(InputStream.class, \"Input Stream\");\n        DataSource dataSource = new PlainTextDataSource(PLAIN_TEXT, MIME_TYPE + \"; charset=UTF-8\");\n\n        Object transferData = handler.getTransferData(unsupportedFlavor, dataSource);\n\n        assertThat(transferData).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void writesPlainTextStringToOutputStream() throws IOException {\n        text_plain handler = new text_plain();\n        ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n\n        handler.writeTo(PLAIN_TEXT, MIME_TYPE + \"; charset=UTF-8\", outputStream);\n\n        assertThat(outputStream.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8.name())).isEqualTo(PLAIN_TEXT);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void rejectsNonStringObjectsWhenWriting() {\n        text_plain handler = new text_plain();\n        ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> handler.writeTo(new byte[] {1, 2, 3}, MIME_TYPE, outputStream))\n                .isInstanceOf(IOException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"DataContentHandler requires String object\");\n    }\n\n    private static void assertPlainStringFlavor(DataFlavor[] flavors) {\n        assertThat(flavors).hasSize(1);\n        assertThat(flavors[0].getRepresentationClass()).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        assertThat(flavors[0].getPrimaryType()).isEqualTo(\"text\");\n        assertThat(flavors[0].getSubType()).isEqualTo(\"plain\");\n        assertThat(flavors[0].getHumanPresentableName()).isEqualTo(\"Text String\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class PlainTextDataSource implements DataSource {\n        private final byte[] content;\n        private final String contentType;\n\n        private PlainTextDataSource(String content, String contentType) {\n            this.content = content.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n            this.contentType = contentType;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getInputStream() {\n            return new ByteArrayInputStream(content);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public OutputStream getOutputStream() throws IOException {\n            throw new IOException(\"Output is not supported\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getContentType() {\n            return contentType;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getName() {\n            return \"plain-text-message\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 897, "output": 1372, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24285, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777668976705, "responseId": "resp_049833e0b00739d70169f51371299c81a3b0f7ccd125a11dbc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_4WlLLPghCo3MMiqV4PAwCv43|fc_049833e0b00739d70169f51378d5fc81a3babbd897bfb6e130", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 4054 bytes to tests/src/javax.mail/mail/1.4/src/test/java/javax_mail/mail/TextPlainTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777668990757}]}
